repo_list.description: Contributed integrations and plugins

Ansible is a radically simple IT automation platform that makes your applications and systems easier to deploy. Avoid writing scripts or custom code to deploy and update your applications— automate in a language that approaches plain English, using SSH, with no agents to install on remote systems.
Cross-platform Ansible role for deploying NetBox, a DCIM/IPAM tool, in a production environment.
Seed data for api.gentoo.org (this is where you create pull requests for new overlays!)
ARA records Ansible Playbook runs and provides intuitive interfaces to browse them
Mirror of git.gentoo.org/proj/catalyst: Catalyst
Factorio Server in Docker
Automate the generation of a Gentoo Linux PXE ready kernel and initramfs
Receive Slack notifications for new releases of your favorite software on GitHub.
A beautiful cross platform Desktop Player for Google Play Music
Ingress controller for nginx
iRedAdmin scripts
Programmatically generated handy kubectl aliases.
Fast way to switch between clusters and namespaces in kubectl!
Alternative Kubernetes UI
Tutorials and Recipes for using Kubernetes Network Policies feature
Setup a kubernetes cluster
implementation of IEEE 802.1ab (LLDP)
Ansible dynamic inventory script for Netbox.
Prometheus RPM Packages
Python high-level interface and ctypes-based bindings for PulseAudio (libpulse)
A python script to be used by Zabbix as a Media-Type for sending notifications to Slack
Gentoo overlay
A funtoo linux overlay for ebuilds I created.
An open-source port of Prince of Persia, based on the disassembly of the DOS version.
